Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.Put all the ingredients in a bowl except the dates and figs, gently bring the mixture together until you have a soft dough-like texture.Add the dates and figs and roll the dough out using a rolling pin to about 4cm/1Â½" deep.Cut out scone shapes with a round cutter and place them on a baking sheet.Brush with egg wash and bake for 20 minutes until golden brown.